40|$|The IEEE 802. 15. 4 {{standard}} for LR-WPANs {{is becoming a}} de-facto {{standard for}} Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs) applications in industrial fields. In this paper, we evaluate the latency performance of the IEEE 802. 15. 4 protocol based on a typical industrial scenario: a star network with 20 devices that send short messages (1 Byte) to the PAN coordinator. We analyzed {{the behavior of the}} GTS mechanism in the standard analytically. The results reveal essential limitations of the standard for low-latency applications in <b>automation</b> <b>environments.</b> According to our findings, we propose an enhanced protocol version that fully supports industry demands on low-latency communication. Our protocol version uses the original physical layer and, thus, can be implemented conveniently using cheap IEEE 802. 15. 4 hardware. The analytical results prove that we are able to meet the guaranteed low latency of 10 ms as specified by typical <b>automation</b> <b>environments...</b>|$|R
